                                                                    27 1451     
 Temperatures = 293.6 400 500 600 700 800 1000 1200 K.              27 1451     
                                                                    27 1451     
 History                                                            27 1451     
 ----------                                                         27 1451     
                                                                    27 1451     
 This library was produced by the Low Energy Interaction Physics    27 1451     
 (LEIP) group at North Carolina State University. The inelastic     27 1451     
 scattering cross section libraries for Be in BeO were fully        27 1451     
 developed using ab-initio and lattice dynamics methods [1]. Eight  27 1451     
 temperatures are available in this library.  The LEAPR module      27 1451     
 from NJOY code system was used to produce File 7, MT = 2, 4 data   27 1451     
 for Be in BeO as a mixed moderator.  Modifications to the LEAPR    27 1451     
 source code were made to calculate the coherent elastic cross      27 1451     
 section for Be in BeO using the Debye Waller matrix method [2].    27 1451     
 By convention, MAT=27 and ZA=127 are used for Be in BeO.           27 1451     
                                                                    27 1451     
                                                                    27 1451     
 Reference                                                          27 1451     
 ----------                                                         27 1451     
                                                                    27 1451     
 1. A.I. Hawari, "Modern Techniques in Inelastic Thermal Neutron    27 1451     
    Scattering Analysis," Nuclear Data Sheets 118 (2014) 172.       27 1451     
 2. Y. Zhu, A. Hawari, "Implementation of a Generalized Coherent    27 1451     
    Elastic Scattering Formulation for Thermal Neutron Scattering   27 1451     
    Analysis", Proceedings of International Conference on Nuclear   27 1451     
    Criticality Safety, Charlotte, NC, September 13-17, 2015.       27 1451     
